Technical Architecture — BharatVaani
Team AlphaForge · PSBs Hackathon Series 2026 (IDEA 2.0 · Union Bank of India)
Overview
BharatVaani is a browser + cloud system. A React branch-desk UI captures microphone audio and streams it over a WebSocket to a FastAPI gateway, which relays it to Google Gemini Live on Vertex AI for real-time speech-to-speech translation. Translated audio and live transcripts stream back to the desk. Each completed turn is enriched by Gemini 2.5 Flash (intent, KYC autofill, PII masking, bilingual summary) and persisted to an audited datastore.

Figure 1 — System architecture and bidirectional data flow.
Components
1. Branch Desk (Client) — React 18 + Vite + TypeScript; AudioWorklet captures PCM16 @16 kHz; WebSocket client; JWT in localStorage; two-pane UI with live transcript and translated-audio playback.
2. Real-Time Gateway — FastAPI (async); /ws/live-translate WebSocket; in-memory session store for hot-path latency; JWT auth + roles (RBAC); orchestrates the Gemini Live session.
3. Gemini Live (Vertex AI) — Model gemini-live-2.5-flash-native-audio; automatic language detection + language memory; Voice Activity Detection (VAD); bidirectional speech ⇄ speech; input & output transcription; authenticated via GCP service account (no rate cap, India-region capable).
4. Banking Intelligence — Gemini 2.5 Flash; per-turn intent detection, KYC field extraction/autofill, PAN/Aadhaar masking, risk flags, talking points, and bilingual summary generation.
5. Datastore — SQLAlchemy 2 (async) over SQLite (dev) / Postgres (prod); tables: users, desk_sessions (redacted turns), interaction_records (bilingual summaries), audit_events.
6. Security & Compliance — JWT + bcrypt auth, role-based access, PII redaction before persistence, full audit log, gitignored credentials; optional on-prem local-LLM (Ollama) deployment so data never leaves the bank.
Data flow (per turn)
1. Mic → AudioWorklet → base64 PCM16 chunks sent over the WebSocket.
2. Gateway forwards audio to the Gemini Live session (send_realtime_input).
3. Gemini detects the language, translates, and streams back audio plus a live transcript (original + translation).
4. On turn-complete, the gateway finalises the turn, runs enrichment, and persists a redacted bilingual record + audit event.
5. Reverse direction (officer English → customer language) uses the same session via language memory.
Technology stack
React · TypeScript · Vite · Web Audio/AudioWorklet · FastAPI · SQLAlchemy 2 (async) · SQLite/Postgres · WebSockets · Google Gemini Live + Gemini 2.5 Flash · Vertex AI · JWT / bcrypt.
Deployment options
Cloud: Vertex AI (India-region) — used for the current working prototype.
On-prem: local LLM via Ollama for strict data residency (designed; roadmap) — data never leaves the bank's network.
